wikipedia_page.main: Keith Barlow (27 August 1890 – 5 April 1930) was an English amateur cricketer and chairman of the paper manufacturer Wiggins Teape. Barlow played two first-class cricket matches for Kent County Cricket Club and was associated with the club as a member of the Committee in the 1920s. He was a right-handed batsman who died in 1930 aged 39 after suffering from ill health for much of his life.
